# 5 Damon Hill               2   2  1:21.300 =1:21.300  0h02m48.514s + 0:03.920
@endnode

@node AGPLapMix "AGPLapMix 0.3"
@{b}AGPLapMix 0.3 (14.1.96)@{ub} by Grant Reeve (reeve1@cs.waikato.ac.nz)

   Aminet:  game/misc/AGPLapTime.lha
      WWW:  http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/utils/AGPLapTime.html
            http://www.xs4all.nl/~rsdi/

Merges separate @{"AGPLaptime" link AGPLapTime} log files together in one log file.  For example,
in the @{"Internet F1GP Championship" link IAF1GPC} all the drivers could send in log files
of their races.  This program can then take all these log files, an
recreate the race as if everybody was racing together.
@endnode

@node AGPLapD "AGPLapD 0.2ß1"
AGPLapD 0.2ß1 (13.11.96)@{ub} by Grant Reeve (reeve1@cs.waikato.ac.nz)

   Aminet:  game/misc/AGPLapTime.lha
      WWW:  http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/utils/AGPLapTime.html
            http://www.xs4all.nl/~rsdi/

A graphical logfile displayer, similar to @{"GPDisplay" link GPDisplay}, for use in
conjunction with @{"AGPLapTime" link AGPLapTime}.
@endnode

@node F1GP-SaveEd "F1GP-SaveEd 1.1"
@{b}F1GP-SaveEd 1.1 (19.10.97)@{ub} by Mario Sarno

   Aminet:  game/misc/F1GP-SaveEd.lha
      WWW:  http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/utils/F1GP-SaveEd.html

Allows you to change various settings in your F1GP end of race save game.
The following settings can be changed:

· The result of every race in the season so far
· The name of every driver, and also which driver is a computer/human
  driver
· The names of every Team, and also their Engine names.  You can also
  change which driver drives for them.
@endnode

@node F1GP-HFED "F1GP-HFED"
@{b}F1GP-HFED (1.2.96)@{ub} by Stephen Leary (9600149L@student.gla.ac.uk)

   WWW:  http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/utils/F1GP-HFED.html

Allows you to alter the helmet images on the driver selection screen in
the game.  Simply design your helmets in any decent paint package and
use this program to convert them into the game.  Maybe useful to some
people I guess, but depends on how often you visit the driver select
screen (ie me -> very rarely :-)
@endnode

@node BKG_DT "F1GP Backdrop Datatype 1.3"
@{b}f1gp_bkg.datatype 1.3 (23.3.99)@{ub} by Oliver Roberts (oliver.roberts@inet.com)

   Aminet:  util/dtype/f1gp_bkg_dt.lha
      WWW:  http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/utils/bkg_dt.html

The F1GP Backdrop datatype is a picture datatype for displaying any of the
backdrop files (filename suffix .bkg) supplied with F1GP.  All of these
images are sized 320x200 and have a 32 colour palette.

Requires Workbench 3.0 or higher.
@endnode

@node Snap "SnapshotF1GP 1.0"
@{b}Snapshot 1.0 (14.12.97)@{ub} by Oliver Roberts (oliver.roberts@inet.com)

   Aminet:  game/misc/SnapshotF1GP.lha
      WWW:  http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/utils/SnapshotF1GP.html

SnapshotF1GP is a program which can be used to take in-game "screenshots"
from F1GP.  As well as being able to take static screenshots, there is an
option which automatically stores multiple successive frames from the game
which can then be used to make an animation

Requires Workbench 2.0 or higher.
@endnode

@node F1GP-RES "F1GP-RES 2.0"
@{b}F1GP-RES 2.0 (29.3.96)@{ub} by Edo Nijmeijer (130588@student.fbk.eur.nl)

   Aminet:  game/misc/F1GP-RES.lha
      WWW:  http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/utils/F1GP-RES.html

F1GP-Record Entry System - mainly a utility for use by @{"Hall of Fame" link HOF}
participants.  Used to store lap times, setups and options used.  Can
scan HoF AmigaGuide files.
@endnode

@node HoF-Ana "HoF-Analyzer 1.4"
@{b}HoF-Analyzer 1.4 (26.4.98)@{ub} by Christophe Macours (s952025@student.ulg.ac.be)

   Aminet:  game/misc/HoF-Analyzer.lha
      WWW:  http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/utils/HoF-Analyzer.html

