@node HoFQ "HoF Qualifier 2.05"
@{b}HoF Qualifier (4.5.98)@{ub} by Micro Dimensions Software

   Aminet:  game/misc/HoFQ.lha
      WWW:  http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/utils/HoFQ.html

Very similiar to @{"F1GP-RES" link F1GP-RES} - in fact, it essentially supercedes it.
HoF Qualifier offers some new different features too, and is fronted by
an OS friendly user interface (F1GP-RES uses AMOS).
@endnode

@node HOF "Amiga F1GP Hall of Fame"
@{b}Amiga F1GP Hall of Fame@{ub} (administrated by Robert Wilson - recoil@globalnet.co.uk)

   Aminet:  docs/hyper
      WWW:  http://www.users.globalnet.co.uk/~recoil/hof/

The latest Internet list of F1GP qualifying lap records from various
participants.  Supplied as an AmigaGuide document.  Released monthly.
@endnode

@node IAF1GPC "Internet Amiga F1GP Championship"
@{b}Internet Amiga F1GP Championship@{ub}
 (administrated by Markus Kruggel - Markus.Kruggel@uni-duisburg.de)

   WWW:  http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/ic/

Compete against other Amiga F1GP players over 100% races.  Players
send in their races times before the posted deadline, and championship
points are calculated according to the fastest times.  To find out more
take a look at the web sites or e-mail Markus.
@endnode

@node PerfBase "Amiga F1GP PerfBase"
@{b}Amiga F1GP PerfBase@{ub} (administrated by Oliver Roberts - oliver.roberts@inet.com)

   WWW:  http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/PerfBase.html

Collection of various @{"AGPPerf" link AGPPerf} perf files, from contenders in the
@{"Hall of Fame" link HOF}, for use with @{"GPDisplay" link GPDisplay}.  Perfs can be downloaded from
the web site.
@endnode
   
@node ML "Amiga F1GP Mailing List"
@{b}Amiga F1GP Mailing List@{ub} (administrated by Oliver Roberts - oliver.roberts@inet.com)

   WWW:  http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/amigaf1gpml.html

The ultimate e-mail based mailing list for F1GP fans.  The mailing list
is used for public discussions about all aspects of F1GP and also for
things related to the Internet Amiga F1GP Championship and Hall of Fame.

To subscribe, send mail to majordomo@thule.no with "subscribe amigaf1gp"
in the message body.  To post messages to the list, send mail to
amigaf1gp@thule.no
@endnode

@node ring "Amiga F1GP Webring"
@{b}Amiga F1GP Webring@{ub} (administrated by Oliver Roberts - oliver.roberts@inet.com)

   WWW:  http://www.nanunanu.org/~oliver/f1gpring/

I'm sure you probably know what a webring is, but just in case you don't,
it's basically a way of linking a number of web pages/sites together which
forms a ring of pages.  Obviously, this particular webring is dedicated to
quality web pages related to F1GP on the Amiga.
@endnode
